How to Run
==========
For q3:
python q3_main.py [output] [squirrel]

if using the output flag, files will be created under the current directory.
if using the squirrel flag, the calculations will be performed on a cute squirrel image,
not on the triangle+cross+rectangle generated image.


Dependencies
============
Assumes scipy, numpy
In order to output graphs, one needs matplotlib
In order to output images, one needs PIL


Files
=======
q3_main.py                      -- runs the search and creates the output files.
q3_gradient_descent.py          -- implementation of GD for minimizing ||Ax - b|| ** 2
q3_conjugate_gradient_method.py -- implementation of CGM for solving A_transpose*A*x = A_transpose*b
blur.py                         -- generates A, b, x. Also contains function to output arrays as images.
